        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 4:11PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farmington, or 10 miles north of Canton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elmwood, Trivoli, Farmington, Yates City, and Middle Grove.

This includes Interstate 74 between mile markers 68 and 71.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
